A: Property Register  This register describes the land and estate comprised in the title. Except as mentioned below, the title includes any legal easements granted by the registered lease but is subject to any rights that it reserves, so far as those easements and rights exist and benefit or affect the registered land.  HILLINGDON 1   (17.03.2004) The Leasehold land shown edged with red on the plan of the above Title filed at the Registry and being 34 Fairfield Road, Uxbridge and Garage 34 (UB8 1AL). NOTE: As to the part tinted blue on the title plan only the first floor flat is included in the title. 2   (17.03.2004) Short particulars of the lease(s) (or under-lease(s)) under which the land is held: Date   : 19 February 2004 Term   : from 19 February 2004 to 24 December 2163 Parties   : (1) Royle Estates (Hoddesdon) Limited (2) Mary Elizabeth Housley NOTE: The original Lease dated 30 May 1975 referred to in the above lease was formerly registered under title number NGL263966 3   An Agreement under Seal dated 11 September 1953 made between (1) Robert Spencer Kirby and Frank William Kirby (First Owners) and (2) Arthur Keith Gibbs and Maurice Frank George Gibbs (Second Owners) contains the following provisions:- "The Second Owners hereby covenant with the First Owners and the First Owners hereby covenant with the Second Owners in manner following (i)   The party wall erect and built as aforesaid as to one longitudial half thereof and as to the buttresses footings and foundations thereto on the said land of the First Owners and as to the other longitudinal half thereof with the buttresses footings and foundations thereto on the said land of the Second Owners has been erected and constructed as to a party wall to be used for the joint purposes of the said new garage building and any buildings that may hereafter be erected contiguous to and against such wall by the Second Owners or their successors in title and they the second owners and First Owners respectively shall have over and in respect of such wall the rights similar to those given to or conferred upon building and adjoining owners by part VI of the London Buildings Acts (Amendment) 1939 with  1 of 3
A: Property Register continued  respect to party walls within the administrative County of London and falling within the scope of the said Act or rights as near thereto as the circumstances will admit but shall have no further or other rights over or in respect of such wall any rule of law or equity to the contrary notwithstanding (ii)   All expenses incurred by the Second Owners and the First Owners respectively in the exercise of their several rights hereunder in respect of the said wall shall be borne and paid by them respectively in the same manner as expenses incurred by building and adjoining owners in respect of party walls falling within the scope of the said Act are thereunder to be borne and paid 2.   In further pursuance of the said Arrangement and for the consideration aforesaid the First Owners as Personal Representatives hereby grant unto the Second Owners and their successors in title in fee simple the right to maintain as now constructed the eaves on the south eastern side of the said new garage building overhanging the land of the First Owners. 3.   And it is hereby agreed and declared that the boundary fences or wall to the rear of the said new garage building between the points marked "B" and "C" on the said plan is the property of and maintainable by the First Owners and their successors in title." NOTE: The land of the first owners is that adjoining the south eastern boundary and the land of the Second Owners is the land in this title The party wall referred to does not affect the land in this title.   The south eastern boundary of the land in this title is affected by the points marked B and C referred to. 4   (17.03.2004) There are appurtenant to the land in this title for the term of 189 years from 25 December 1974 (determinable) the rights granted by a Deed dated 19 February 2004 made between (1) Fairfield Place (Uxbridge) Management Company Limited and (2) Mary Elizabeth Housley.  NOTE: Copy filed.  5   (17.03.2004) There are excepted from the effect of registration all estates, rights, interests, powers and remedies arising upon, or by reason of, any dealing made in breach of the prohibition or restriction against dealings therewith inter vivos contained in the Lease. 6   (17.03.2004) The lessor's title is registered. 7   Unless otherwise mentioned the title includes any legal easements granted by the registered lease(s) but is subject to any rights that it reserves, so far as those easements and rights exist and benefit or affect the registered land.  B: Proprietorship Register  This register specifies the class of title and identifies the owner. It contains any entries that affect the right of disposal.  Title absolute  1   (17.03.2004) PROPRIETOR: MARY ELIZABETH HOUSLEY of 34 Fairfield Road, Uxbridge Middx UB8 1AL.  C: Charges Register  This register contains any charges and other matters that affect the land.  1   A Conveyance of the freehold estate in the land in this title and other land dated 27 November 1868 made between (1) Thomas Coath and (2) William Wills contains covenants details of which are set out in the schedule of restrictive covenants hereto.  Title number AGL126671  2 of 3
Schedule of restrictive covenants  1   The following are details of the covenants contained in the Conveyance dated 27 November 1868 referred to in the Charges Register:- "AND the said William Wills doth hereby for himself his heirs executors administrators and assigns covenant with the said Thomas Coath his heirs and assigns.   That he the said William Wills his heirs and assigns will keep observe and perform the said Stipulations of Sale hereinbefore recited or referred to so far as the same respectively relate to the use and enjoyment of the said Two several pieces or parcels of Land hereinbefore mentioned to be hereby granted and conveyed or intended so to be That the respective Purchasers should within Three calendar months from the Eleventh day of November instant make and afterwards maintain good and sufficient Fences on the side or sides of their respective Lots as shewn on the said Plan which Fences should not be more than Eight feet high.   That no Building on the Several Lots should be erected nearer to the Road or Roads in front than the Building Line shewn on the said Plan and which as to the said Lots 18 and 19 is set back Twenty feet from the south west front against Pages Lane.   That there should not be erected on either of the said Lots (except on Lots 14 and 53) more than Two Houses and not on either of the same Lots 14 and 53 more than Four houses and no House to be erected should be used as a Tavern Public House Beer Shop or as a shop of any description.   That the Sale of Beer should not be allowed on any Lot.   That no Bricks should be made or burnt or Brick Kiln used on any Lot.   That no House to be erected on any of the Lots 1 to 3 inclusive should be of less value than Five hundred pounds on any of the Lots 18 to 24 Inclusive of less value than Five hundred pounds on any of the Lots 4 to 17 inclusive of less value than Four hundred pounds on any of the Lots 25 to 31 inclusive of less value than Four hundred pounds on any of the said Lots 32 to 59 inclusive of less value than Three hundred and fifty pounds or on any of the Lots 60 to 76 inclusive of less value than Three hundred pounds.   The value of a Building to be the amount of its net first cost in material and labor of construction only but these Stipulations were not to preclude the purchaser from building Stables or appurtenances to the principal House on any adjoining Lot." NOTE 1: The land in this title forms part of lots 18 and 19 referred to above NOTE 2: Pages Lane is now known as Harefield Road.  End of register  Title number AGL126671  3 of 3
